      "id": "installation",
      "name": "Installation",
      "content": "## Quick Start with Docker\n\nThe fastest way to get started with Dependency-Track is using Docker Compose:\n\n```bash\n# Download the official Docker Compose file\ncurl -LO https://dependencytrack.org/docker-compose.yml\n\n# Start Dependency-Track\ndocker-compose up -d\n\n# Access the web interface\n# URL: http://localhost:8080\n# Default credentials: admin/admin\n```\n\n## Installation Methods\n\n### Docker Deployment\n- **Recommended**: Use official Docker images\n- **Scalable**: Supports container orchestration\n- **Easy Updates**: Pull latest images for updates\n- **Production Ready**: Includes PostgreSQL database\n\n### WAR Deployment\n- Download WAR file from GitHub releases\n- Deploy to Java servlet container (Tomcat 9+, Jetty)\n- Requires external PostgreSQL database\n- Manual configuration required\n\n### Kubernetes\n- Official Helm charts available\n- Supports horizontal scaling\n- Production-grade deployments\n- Persistent storage configuration\n\n## System Requirements\n\n### Minimum Requirements\n- **Memory**: 4GB RAM minimum (8GB+ recommended)\n- **Storage**: 20GB available disk space\n- **Java**: OpenJDK 11 or higher\n- **Database**: PostgreSQL 10+ (included in Docker setup)\n\n### Network Requirements\n- **Outbound HTTPS**: Access to vulnerability data sources\n- **Port 8080**: Web interface (configurable)\n- **Port 8081**: API endpoint (configurable)\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Database Setup\n```bash\n# PostgreSQL configuration example\nALPINE_DATABASE_MODE=external\nALPINE_DATABASE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/dtrack\nALPINE_DATABASE_DRIVER=org.postgresql.Driver\nALPINE_DATABASE_USERNAME=dtrack\nALPINE_DATABASE_PASSWORD=changeme\n```\n\n### Security Configuration\n- Configure HTTPS/TLS certificates\n- Set up authentication providers\n- Configure API keys and tokens\n- Enable audit logging\n\n## Post-Installation\n\n1. **Initial Setup**: Change default admin password\n2. **Data Sources**: Configure vulnerability intelligence feeds\n3. **Teams & Permissions**: Set up user access controls\n4. **Notifications**: Configure alert channels\n5. **Integrations**: Connect CI/CD tools and scanners",
